Now we can put the vectors $\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 2 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} -3 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$ as columns of a matrix : \begin{align*}
    \mathbf{P} &= \begin{pmatrix} 1 & -3 \\ 2 & 1 \end{pmatrix} 
\end{align*> <answer>Then we can find the inverse of the matrix by taking the reciprocal of the determinants: \begin{align*}
    \mathbf{P}^{-1} &= \frac{1}{5} \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 3 \\ -2 & 1 \end{pmatrix} 
\end{align*</answer>

